text: Greene County is a county in the U.S. state of Georgia. As of the 2020 census, the population was 18,915. The county seat is Greensboro. The county was founded on February 3, 1786 and is named for Nathanael Greene, an American Revolutionary War major general. == References == Category:18th-century establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:1786 establishments in the United States Category:Georgia (U.S. state) counties
title: Greene County, Georgia
